Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BalanceOf
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when account is queried
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the balance for that account
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when account is zero address
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return 0
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ TotalSupply
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when queried
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the total token supply
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Allowance
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when owner and spender are queried
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the remaining allowance for that (owner, spender)

Approve
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the spender is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the spender is not the zero address
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set the caller's allowance for the spender to value
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit an {Approval} event
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

Transfer
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the receiver is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the receiver is not the zero address
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ given when the sender's balance is less than the transfer amount
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ given when the sender's balance is greater than, or equal to, the transfer amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the amount is zero
        в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event
        в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should not change balances
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the amount is > 0
            в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the sender's balance by the transfer amount
            в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment the receiver's balance by the transfer amount
            в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

TransferFrom
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the sender is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the receiver is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when both sender and receiver are non-zero addresses
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ given allowance < amount
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ given allowance >= amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ given balance < amount
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ given balance >= amount
            в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when amount is zero
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should not change balances
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should not decrement allowance
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event
            в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
            в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when amount > 0 and allowance is max uint256
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the sender's balance by the transfer amount
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment the receiver's balance by the transfer amount
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should not change allowance
            в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event
            в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the amount is greater than zero and allowance is finite
                в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the allowance by the transfer amount
                в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the sender's balance by the transfer amount
                в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment the receiver's balance by the transfer amount
                в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event
                в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

Mint
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account to mint to is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account to mint to is not the zero address
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ given the mint amount would overflow total supply
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ given the mint amount does not overflow total supply
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment total supply by the mint amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment the account's balance by the mint amount
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event from zero address to the account

Burn
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account to burn from is the zero address
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account to burn from is not the zero address
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account balance is less than the burn amount
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account balance is greater than or equal to the burn amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement the account balance by the burn amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement total supply by the burn amount
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {Transfer} event to the zero address

Metadata
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Name
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when set (via Mod)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the token name
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Symbol
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when set (via Mod)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the token symbol
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Decimals
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when set (via Mod)
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the number of decimals

Bridgeable
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ CrosschainMint
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller does not have trusted-bridge role
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when account is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller has trusted-bridge role and account is not zero
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment total supply and account balance by the amount
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit {Transfer} from zero and {CrosschainMint}
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ CrosschainBurn
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller does not have trusted-bridge role
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from is zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from balance is less than the amount
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InsufficientBalance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller has trusted-bridge role and from has sufficient balance
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement total supply and from balance by the amount
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit {Transfer} to zero and {CrosschainBurn}
в””в”Ђв”Ђ CheckTokenBridge
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InvalidBridgeAccount
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller does not have trusted-bridge role
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InvalidBridgeAccount
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when caller has trusted-bridge role
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not revert

Permit
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Nonces
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when owner has not used permit
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return 0
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when owner has used permit
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the incremented nonce
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ DOMAIN_SEPARATOR
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when queried
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the EIP-712 domain separator (name, version, chainId, verifyingContract)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Permit
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when spender is zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC20InvalidSpender
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when deadline has passed
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC2612InvalidSignature
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when signature is invalid (wrong signer or malformed)
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC2612InvalidSignature
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when signature is valid and deadline not passed
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set allowance(owner, spender) to value
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increment nonces(owner)
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit {Approval}